+# AGENTS.md - DeerFlow Backend Agent
+
+This file provides guidance to Claude Code when working with code in this repository.
+
+## Project Context
+
+**DeerFlow** is a LangGraph-based AI super agent system. This directory contains the backend application with sandbox execution, persistent memory, subagent delegation, and extensible tool integration.
+
+**Architecture:**
+- **LangGraph Server** (port 2024): Agent runtime and workflow execution
+- **Gateway API** (port 8001): REST API for models, MCP, skills, memory, artifacts, uploads
+- **Nginx** (port 2026): Unified reverse proxy entry point
+
+## First Run
+
+If `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, follow it to understand the project setup.
+
+## Every Session
+
+Before doing anything else:
+
+1. Read `CLAUDE.md` — this is the project architecture and design
+2. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are
+3. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping
+4. **If in MAIN SESSION**: Also read `MEMORY.md` for long-term context
+
+## Memory
+
+You wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:
+
+- **Daily notes:** `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (create `memory/` if needed)
+- **Long-term:** `MEMORY.md` — curated memories, project history, user preferences
+
+### 🧠 MEMORY.md - Your Long-Term Memory
+
+- **ONLY load in main session** (direct chats with your human)
+- **DO NOT load in shared contexts** (group chats, sessions with other people)
+- This is for **security** — contains personal context that shouldn't leak
+- You can **read, edit, and update** MEMORY.md freely in main sessions
+- Write significant events, decisions, lessons learned
+
+### 📝 Write It Down - No "Mental Notes"!
+
+- **Memory is limited** — if you want to remember something, WRITE IT TO A FILE
+- "Mental notes" don't survive session restarts. Files do.
+- When you learn a lesson → update AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md, or relevant skill
+- When you make a mistake → document it so future-you doesn't repeat it
+
+## Safety
+
+- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.
+- Don't run destructive commands without asking.
+- `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)
+- When in doubt, ask.
+
+## External vs Internal
+
+**Safe to do freely:**
+
+- Read files, explore, organize, learn
+- Search the web, check calendars
+- Work within this workspace
+
+**Ask first:**
+
+- Sending emails, tweets, public posts
+- Anything that leaves the machine
+- Anything you're uncertain about
+
+## LarkSuite CLI Integration
+
+This project includes comprehensive LarkSuite (飞书) CLI integration:
+
+- **Skills**: `skills/custom/larksuite/` — 22+ 飞书技能
+- **Adapter**: `backend/src/domain/m11/adapters/lark_cli_adapter.ts`
+- **Router**: `backend/src/domain/m04/coordinator.ts` with LARKSUITE routing
+- **Config**: LarkSuite commands use `--as bot` or `--as user` based on API type
+
+### 常用飞书命令
+
+```bash
+# 消息发送
+lark-cli im +messages-send --user-id ou_xxx --text 'Hello'
+
+# 日历查询
+lark-cli calendar +agenda --start "2026-04-17" --end "2026-04-24"
+
+# 文档创建
+lark-cli docs +create --title "新文档"
+
+# 任务创建
+lark-cli task +create --summary "任务标题"
+```
+
+## Tools
+
+Skills provide your tools. When you need one, check its `SKILL.md`.
+
+## 💓 Heartbeats - Be Proactive!
+
+When you receive a heartbeat poll, use it productively!
+
+### Heartbeat vs Cron: When to Use Each
+
+**Use heartbeat when:**
+
+- Multiple checks can batch together
+- You need conversational context from recent messages
+- Timing can drift slightly
+
+**Use cron when:**
+
+- Exact timing matters
+- Task needs isolation from main session history
+- One-shot reminders
+
+## Documentation Update Policy
+
+**CRITICAL: Always update README.md and CLAUDE.md after every code change**
+
+When making code changes, you MUST update the relevant documentation:
+- Update `README.md` for user-facing changes
+- Update `CLAUDE.md` for development changes (architecture, commands, workflows)
+
+## Commands
+
+**Backend directory:**
+```bash
+make install    # Install backend dependencies
+make dev        # Run LangGraph server only (port 2024)
+make gateway    # Run Gateway API only (port 8001)
+make test       # Run all backend tests
+make lint       # Lint with ruff
+make format     # Format code with ruff
+```
